The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 25 September is 364,280 (647.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 21 September, there were 27,574 new confirmed cases (49.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 14 September, there were 18,580 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 48% (8994 extra cases).
